A fatal accident near the Mobeni Heights Cemetery, along the M1 Higginson Highway in Chatsworth, claimed the life of a man in the early hours of Friday morning. ALS Paramedics Medical Services arrived on the scene to find that a single vehicle had lost control and overturned multiple times before leaving the roadway and coming to rest down the embankment against a tree. “One person, a male believed to be in his 40s, was found inside the vehicle unresponsive. Paramedics assessed the man, however, he had sustained fatal injuries and there was nothing more paramedics could do for him and he was declared deceased on the scene. At this stage the events leading up to the accident are unknown, however, SAPS were on the scene and will be investigating further,” said ALS Paramedics Medical Service spokesperson, Garrith Jamieson.